    "body": "<!--To help us understand and resolve your issue, please fill out the form to the best of your ability. Feel free to delete the sections that do not apply.-->\r\n\r\n**Description of the problem**\r\nPlotting points from a file with locations and symbols can fail because the latter columns are not read.\r\n\r\n<!-- Please be as detailed as you can when describing an issue. The more information we have, the easier it will be for us to track this down. -->\r\n\r\n**Full script that generated the error**\r\n```bash\r\necho \"5 5 0.1c t\" > temp.txt\r\ngmt plot -R0/10/0/10 -BWSne -Baf -JX4c temp.txt  -S -i0,1,2,3 -W1p,black -png test\r\n```\r\nThis generates an empty frame, not to mention using other arbitrary order of columns selected from a number of columns.\r\n\r\nHowever, reading all columns by default does work:\r\n```bash\r\ngmt plot -R0/10/0/10 -BWSne -Baf -JX4c temp.txt  -S  -W1p,black -png test\r\n```\r\n\r\n, which plots a triangle at the center.\r\n\r\n**Expected outcome**\r\n\r\n<!--A description of the expected outcome from the above script.-->\r\n\r\n**System information**\r\n\r\n* Operating system: Linux\r\n* GMT version (`gmt --version`):\r\n6.1.1\r\n",
